<br>
Guys, for those of you that aren't current epic holders and are thinking it's impossible, this thing is totally do-able, even if you are not in a guild.  You just gotta want it bad enough, I think.  The success in PoA w/ the magi crew is evidence enough of what you guys can do when you band together, put in the time and effort, and work hard.  I'll admit, I got lucky on the PoH staff (and I recognize as my friend Khalen told me the other day that this will be the major bottleneck for epic-desiring magi) but the rest is completely do-able in a group or two.  The PoH staff will be a problematic piece for some as it takes a standard-sized PoH raid to clear through to the 3-day, not-sure-if-she'll-drop-the-staff Magi P'Tasa spawn.  Otherwise, the rest isn't as big of a problem.  As demonstrated, the crown can be taken care of through a fairly long and painstaking effort of 12+ magicians; perhaps more if you raid the entire zone throughout, first.  The two items in Kedge can be done w/ all Magician parties (Phinney is L53 and dispels, but otherwise he's cake), all of the items in Najena are just a matter of camping time, and I believe the CoH torch can be done in a weekend-long raid schedule w/ several magi -- Neh'Ashiir drops it seemingly around 35% or so of the time (someone correct me here) but black reavers are do-able w/ a nicely-sized magician group or two.  Plus, once the raid gets into the locked room on the sky level, it's a very good XP camp as the zone has an XP bonus.  Reaver respawn time is 2hrs.<br>
<br>
Real quick, I also wanted to quickly mention all the three support people (outside of the magician crew that is) that have still stuck around with us during our 2 to 3 week long stint in PoA:  Grumpie, L54 (will be 53 soon after all the DT's this crazy guy takes for kicks) warrior, Synthalia L60 cleric, and Mogollon L55/56 shaman -- these three are a class act.  Without them we wouldn't have had the success we've had and I wouldn't have my own orb.  Btw, we had one more crown drop last night and Zanta won it! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That makes for 18 total in 7 clearings.  Just a few more nights to go and we'll finally be able to call the raid and go on to bigger and better things.<br>
